title: For Sale/Trade:  BNIB Beretta 90-Two .40 S&W
postcontent: This is a brand new in the box and unfired Beretta 90-Two chambered in .40 S&W.As most Beretta enthusiasts know, this is one the best pistols ever made by Beretta but the most poorly marketed, starting with the name.  Model 90-Two was indistinguishable from the venerable Model 92; for this reason, the pistol never gained traction with the public.For those who say they only want a 9mm, you should take a closer look at the .40 S&W.  First, this round delivers 40% more energy on target than the 9mm.  In fact, .40 S&W has as much energy as the slower velocity .45 ACP.  This is why law enforcement pioneered the .40 S&W and why the next generation of U.S. miliatry sidearms will probably be .40 S&W.As for cost, .40 S&W is only marginally more expensive than 9mm: $2+/box.  That's a small price to pay for the massive increase in effectiveness.  In order words, you get a lot more bang for the buck.Slim-grips are available for an additional $30.00; steel guide rod is available for an additonal $30.00.  Or, buy both upgrades for $50.00.Add $25.00 for S&H to your FFL.Email, call or text: 8zero6 58four 379two.

Details
Action: Single Action, Double Action Semi-Automatic • Finish: Matte Black • Barrel: 3.2" • Sights: Fixed front, Adjustable Rear • Magazine(s): 2 - 12rd • Grips: Polymer • Weight: 22 oz. • Overall Length: 6.24" • MSRP: $301.52 With its lightweight 22 oz. polymer frame, thin profile, and ramped 3.2 inch barrel, the newly designed Millennium G2 is the ideal concealed carry handgun. The Millennium G2 features an accessory rail, high-profile sights, an aggressive, textured grip and melted edges for added comfort and easy concealment. Taurus Security System (TSS)s Taurus family of semi-auto pistols now feature the Taurus Security System, which provides instant-ready defense with built-in ability to secure your pistol and make it inoperable at the turn of a key. When the Security System is engaged, the pistol cannot be fired or cocked and the gun's manual safety cannot be disengaged. As with our revolver Security System, the device is part of the firearm and cannot be lost, and the same special Security Key works for both the revolver and pistol Systems (two keys come with each gun). To engage: simply insert the Key into the button on the rear or side of the pistol and rotate one-quarter turn clockwise. This engages the Security System. The manual safety cannot be moved and the trigger cannot be pulled. To disengage: simply rotate the key one-quarter turn back. This releases the Security System, yet leaves the pistol's manual safety in the "safe" position until you are ready to release it yourself and fire the gun. Loaded Chamber Indicator Taurus provides a loaded chamber indicator on all new compact, medium and large frame pistols. As with all Taurus safety and security innovations, the indicator in no way interferes with the operation of your pistol and is provided at no extra cost, but gives you an "at-a-glance" verification that there is a round in the chamber. When a round is in the chamber, the ejector pops out of the slide, exposing a red strip just behind the ejection port. While any loaded chamber indicator is no substitute for common sense and safe firearm handling, it is one more example of Taurus' commitment to outstanding firearms.
